21/02/2005
TIRANA, Albania -- The leader of the main opposition Democratic Party (DP), Sali Berisha, does not rule out the possibility of assuming the prime minister's post, if the DP wins the next parliamentary elections and returns to power. In an interview Friday (18 February), he said the party's government platform includes economic reforms aimed at creating new jobs, improving the investment climate and enhancing small businesses. 
Also Friday, Ombudsman Ermir Dobjani outlined his priorities, after being given a second term. They include improving prison conditions and protecting prisoners' human rights. (Albanian News - 19/02/05)
